The '''School of Molecular Bioscience''' is a constituent body of the [[Sydney Faculty of Science|Faculty of Science]] at the [[University of Sydney]], [[Australia]]. It was established in its present form in 2001.
==History== The School was renamed the School of Molecular Bioscience from the School of Molecular and Microbial Biosciences on 11 February 2010.<ref name="about_school">[http://sydney.edu.au/science/molecular_bioscience/about_the_school/history.php A SHORT HISTORY OF THE SCHOOL]</ref> The School of Molecular and Microbial Biosciences was formed in 2001 within the Faculty of Science from the amalgamation of the Department of Biochemistry (from the Faculty of Science) and the Department of Microbiology (from the Faculty of Agriculture).<ref name="about_school" />
